<br>
Winds of Gellid + Iceflame of E'Ci....<br>
<br>
<br>
I'd just like to point out that neither focus items, nor bard song, nor ice flame affect the damage of PBAE spells or Pillars or Rains in anyway at all and that attempting to correct folks about something when its you that are clueless is lame.<br>
<br>
And on balance..<br>
<br>
I couldnt care less if I do 10 percent more/less damage or whatever than any particular class, what I care about is whether or not its fun.  Make it fun, thats all I ask.  Killing 87487832 of the same mob to get somewhere (VT, Saryn sol ro) isnt fun, its work.  Work does not equal fun.<br>
<br>
An example of what I call fun. Crypt of decay.<br>
<br>
Its a challenging zone for soloers, groups, and raids. <br>
Whether you are doing the high priest ultor cycle (pesky skellies!) or Bertoxx ring there was always that feeling that you needed to be on top of your game in order to succeed.<br>
I can't quite explain why it is that fighting the constant spawns in the Bertoxx encounter is fun and killing the 872272 mobs in vt is mindless drudgery but I bet most would agree with me.  Perhaps its that with bert you absolutely have to keep the trash down and pull those kings asap and with vt one gets the feeling that it really doesnt matter when you do it, its just something you have to do.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
