</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=starlettwiz>StarlettWiz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/1/03 9:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Diversity VS Beancounting , thoughts on class balance</span><hr size=1> I must say that I love Maevenniia's Familiar suggestions!<br>
<br>
How about a few more utility spells for wizards just for 'fun'?  I use my Eye of Tallon for scouting ahead in dungeon crawl groups, reporting on mob placement and that often gives me a greater sense of achievement than landing a big crit.<br>
<br>
How about:<br>
Flight - Self only line of spells that works similar to levitate but you can also move up/down at will.<br>
<br>
Translocate Mob to Caster - Translocates a mob to the wizard (yes, getting a lot of aggro in the process) but only with a short range.  Useful in some instances for splitting mobs, but not to bypass content.<br>
<br>
Translocate Mob to Bind - Similar to above, but sends a mob back to its spawn point (with aggro wiped?).  Add level restriction so it affects lower level mobs and this becomes a handy ability rather than needing to replace a chanter/bard for mezzes.<br>
<br>
Illusion: Drake - Flappys are in the global file, so how about this as an AA (combine with flight spell?).<br>
<br>
I don't WANT bigger nukes, I want better toys <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Starlett - 61 Wizard -  Vazaelle<br>
